Diagnosis:
This species can be recognized by the shape of surstyli in dorsal view, constricted in middle (
Fig. 24A
), broadened in basal third in lateral view (
Fig. 24C‒D
); epandrium longer than wide in dorsal view (
Fig. 24A
); sub- epandrial sclerite long and broad in ventral view (
Fig. 24B
); gonopods equal in height (
Fig. 24B
); phallic guide long, curved to abdominal sternite in lateral view (
Fig. 24C‒D
).
